@startuml cruise_set_to_longitudinal_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Cruise Set To Longitudinal Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> SCC -> VCU -> ESC / CLU)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Cruise" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "SCC\ncruise state owner" as SCC #FCE8FF
participant "VCU\nlongitudinal speed owner" as VCU #E8F7E8
participant "ESC\nbrake pressure owner" as ESC #FFE6E6
participant "CLU\nspeed / set readback" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Cruise Input ==

Driver -> Panel : Select cruise mode and target speed
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Cmd::cruiseStateCmd
Panel -> Panel : Write Cmd::cruiseSetSpeedCmd
deactivate Panel

== SCC Cruise Ownership ==

activate SCC
Panel -> SCC : Cmd::cruiseStateCmd / Cmd::cruiseSetSpeedCmd
SCC -> SCC : clamp command and apply speed-limit cap
SCC -> SCC : derive cruiseState / cruiseSetSpeed
SCC -> VCU : Powertrain::cruiseState
SCC -> VCU : Powertrain::cruiseSetSpeed
note right of SCC
Representative rules
- ON/DECEL command normalization
- lower bound 30 when cruise active
- upper bound by speed limit
end note
deactivate SCC

== VCU Longitudinal Ownership ==

activate VCU
SCC -> VCU : Powertrain::cruiseState / cruiseSetSpeed
VCU -> VCU : manualCruiseActive when\nignition on, gear >= D,\nno pedal input, cruise state > 0
VCU -> VCU : release manual panel speed target\nwhen cruise becomes active
VCU -> VCU : derive speed / drive state
VCU -> ESC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
VCU -> CLU : Chassis::vehicleSpeed / driveState
note right of VCU
Representative logic
- manualCruiseActive
- gManualVehicleSpeedTarget reset
- externalSpeedOverride / owner vehicle speed
end note
deactivate VCU

== Brake / Readback Side ==

activate ESC
VCU -> ESC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
ESC -> ESC : update brake response only if brake pedal or assist floor applies
deactivate ESC

activate CLU
SCC -> CLU : Powertrain::cruiseSetSpeed readback
VCU -> CLU : Chassis::vehicleSpeed
CLU -> Panel : meter / live set / speed readback
deactivate CLU

Driver <- Panel : Cruise set and vehicle speed move in one longitudinal chain

note over Driver, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. Driver sets cruise mode and set-speed
2. SCC owns cruise state and set-speed normalization
3. VCU owns longitudinal speed response
4. ESC follows downstream brake dynamics only when needed
5. CLU and panel show live set-speed and vehicle speed
end note

@enduml
